HEADWORD: Beriberi
<hw>Be`ri*be"ri</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Singhalese
<ets>beri</ets> weakness.]</ety> <def>An acute disease occurring in
India, characterized by multiple inflammatory changes in the nerves,
producing great muscular debility, a painful rigidity of the limbs, and
cachexy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

